HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 291
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Doris Voitier for more than fifty years of service to St.
Bernard Parish public schools
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Doris Voitier for more than fifty years of service to St. Bernard Parish public
3 schools.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Doris Voitier for her dedication to public
5 education and to commend her for more than fifty years of service to St. Bernard Parish
6 public schools; and
7 WHEREAS, Doris is a proud graduate of Mount Carmel Academy; she attended the
8 University of New Orleans, where she earned a bachelor's degree in mathematics education
9 and a master's degree in curriculum and instruction; she completed additional postgraduate
10 course work in educational leadership; and
11 WHEREAS, Ms. Voitier began her career in St. Bernard Parish as a math teacher and
12 later moved into administration, where she served as an assistant principal, principal,
13 supervisor of secondary education, assistant superintendent, and superintendent; and
14 WHEREAS, Hurricane Katrina devastated St. Bernard Parish just one year after
15 Ms. Voitier began serving as superintendent; she played an instrumental role in assisting the
16 rapid reopening of schools, providing stability and hope for returning families, and helping
17 lead the recovery of the parish; she received national recognition for her leadership during
18 the recovery efforts and was presented with the John F. Kennedy Profile in Courage Award;
19 and
