1 WHEREAS, under Ms. Voitier's leadership, the St. Bernard Parish School District
2 has consistently demonstrated academic growth and innovation and a strong commitment
3 to student success; and
4 WHEREAS, Ms. Voitier has served as a member and past president of the Louisiana
5 Board of Elementary and Secondary Education, where she helped shape education policy
6 for students across the state; and
7 WHEREAS, Doris Voitier's career reflects her belief that strong public schools are
8 the foundation of strong communities, and she is deserving of recognition for her
9 outstanding commitment to serving students, families, and educators of St. Bernard Parish.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
11 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Doris Voitier for more than fifty years of
12 service to St. Bernard Parish public schools and does hereby extend sincere wishes that she
13 remain prosperous in all of her endeavors.
